i/p a char:
Scanner s=new Scanner(System.in);
char c=s.next().charAt(0);

equals():
if(s1.equals(s2))
System.out.print("equal");

equalsIgnoreCase():
if(s1.equalsIgnoreCase(s2))
System.out.print("equal");

replace(char c1,char c2):
System.out.print(s1.replace(ch1,ch2));

charAt():
System.out.print(s1.charAt(position));

toUpperCase():
System.out.print(s1.toUpperCase());

substring(int,int): //note: start index is inclusive and end index is exclusive
System.out.print(s1.substring(0,3));

split():
String s1="hi:helo";
String[] s=s1.split(":");
//for printing
for(String s2:s)
System.out.print(s2+" ");

toCharArray():
String s="hello";
char[] arr=s.toCharArray();
//for printing
for(char c:arr)
System.out.print(c+" ");

Char array to string:
char[] arr="hello\0"
String s=new String(arr);

conatins():
String s="hi hy";
String s1="hi";
if(s.contains(s1))
System.out.print("yes");

repeat():
String s="hi hy";
int n=3;
System.out.print(s.repeat(n));

Note:
String class does not inbuilt rev func whereas string builder has. 
Also String class does toCharArray func whereas string builder does not has.

string to string builder:
String s="hi";
StringBuilder str = new StringBuilder(s);
System.out.print(str);
